{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"HTML Case Study: Portfolio","slug":"html-case-studies","subject":"HTML","category":"Web Development","level":"Advanced","estimated_read_time":"20 minutes","prerequisites":["HTML Project Structure"],"learning_objectives":["Build a complete Landing Page","Combine all concepts (Header, Nav, Section, Form, Footer)","Review code structure"],"theory":"# Real World Case Study: Personal Portfolio\n\nWe will construct the blueprint for a standard portfolio page.\n\n## 1. Structure\n*   **Header**: Logo and Navigation.\n*   **Hero Section**: Intro text and photo.\n*   **About Section**: Text and Skills list.\n*   **Projects Section**: Grid of project previews.\n*   **Contact Section**: A Form.\n*   **Footer**: Social links.\n\n## 2. The Code\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>My Portfolio</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n    <!-- Navigation -->\n    <header>\n        <nav>\n            <ul>\n                <li><a href=\"#hero\">Home</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"#projects\">Projects</a></li>\n                <li><a href=\"#contact\">Contact</a></li>\n            </ul>\n        </nav>\n    </header>\n\n    <!-- Hero -->\n    <main>\n        <section id=\"hero\">\n            <h1>Hello, I'm Dev.</h1>\n            <p>I build websites.</p>\n            <a href=\"#contact\">Hire Me</a>\n        </section>\n\n        <!-- Projects -->\n        <section id=\"projects\">\n            <h2>My Work</h2>\n            <article>\n                <h3>Project A</h3>\n                <p>An amazing app.</p>\n            </article>\n        </section>\n\n        <!-- Contact -->\n        <section id=\"contact\">\n            <h2>Contact Me</h2>\n            <form action=\"/send\" method=\"POST\">\n                <input type=\"email\" required placeholder=\"Your Email\">\n                <textarea></textarea>\n                <button>Send</button>\n            </form>\n        </section>\n    </main>\n\n    <!-- Footer -->\n    <footer>\n        <p>&copy; 2024 Dev.</p>\n    </footer>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n```","syntax":"Full Project","examples":[{"code":"See above.","output":"A complete semantic page structure.","explanation":"Notice correct nesting: header/main/footer at root. section/article inside main."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Skipping main tag","correction":"Always wrap the primary central content in <main>.","example":"<body><main>...</main></body>"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"How would you structure a landing page?","difficulty":"Intermediate","answer":"Header with Nav, Main containing Sections (Hero, Features, Testimonials), and a Footer. Using semantic tags throughout."}],"practice_problems":[{"difficulty":"Advanced","problem":"Copy the Case Study code into a file 'portfolio.html' and open it. Then add CSS to make the nav horizontal.","hint":"nav ul { display: flex; }","solution":"N/A (Project)"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Freelancing","description":"This structure is the template for 90% of small business websites.","code":"Standard Layout"}],"exam_notes":["Logical flow: Head -> Body -> Header -> Main -> Footer","Use IDs for local navigation (#contact)","Forms for contact","Articles for items"],"summary":"This case study ties everything together. We used headings for structure, lists for navigation, forms for contact, and semantic tags to wrap it all up. This is a production-ready HTML skeleton.","order":27},"courseTutorials":[{"slug":"html-document-structure","path":"content/html/html-document-structure.json","title":"HTML Document Structure","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":2},{"slug":"html-comments","path":"content/html/html-comments.json","title":"HTML Comments","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":3},{"slug":"html-editors","path":"content/html/html-editors.json